Ask HN: Predictions on the Crypto/Blockchain Ecosystem?
text:
It’s been almost a decade since the original Bitcoin paper and we still haven’t seen any tangible real life applications in the world of blockchain except huge speculations which resulted in a trillion dollar unregulated industry.

Putting aside my skeptic view, I do see the value of decentralization in certain areas and we need to keep pushing the innovation in this space despite the recent fraudulent events.

I would like to hear what the community thinks about this. Is the whole thing been a Ponzi scheme to begin with from the beginning or do you think there’s a need for alternative economy / decentralized infrastructure to exist in the current world setup?

I am not looking for yes or no answers but more like rational arguments behind your opinions

Ask HN: What newsletters or blogs do you follow about generative AI?
text:
I'm very interested in generative AI especially for making assets for games or interactive content. I am on the look out for a proper (ideally open source) implementation of NVIDIA's Magic3D[0] - or something that gets close to it, but it's frustrating to search. I found Stable DreamFusion[1] but I don't think it's there yet.

Are there newsletters, blogs, youtube channels or even podcasts that I can subscribe to in order to get an email when a new cool generative AI toy comes out for me to experiment with? Papers are interesting, but code or executables are preferred.

Thanks in advance!

[0] https://deepimagination.cc/Magic3D/

[1] https://medium.com/mlearning-ai/how-to-easily-run-dreamfusion-ai-text-to-3d-for-free-32e6cecb82d
